snippet.textDisplay:
I have just listened to the most ridiculous comment I have ever listened to about the floods. On the BBC News. Someone said this is the new norm, we have to get used to it. Why do we have to get used to it? because were not intelligent enough to control our population and adopt a system that is compatible with the environment we live in.


so we come back with stupid comments like this, so much for claiming to be an intelligent species then.

The key to our future is not to get used to this abnormal weather. But to understand why it is happening and alter our behaviour so we can stop it from increasing and start it decreasing.

Which is by reducing our population down to an acceptable level that this island can naturally support, getting rid of this ridiculous incompatible system of endless growth so a few people can live in a lap of luxury.

How can we claim to be an intelligent species when we put greed and selfishness and making money higher on the list than our own existence.

I challenge the BBC to start the ball rolling in the right direction.
We are supposed to be adult intelligent people, so let's have an open debate on prime-time television about population reduction in a calm and rational constructive adult fashion, and talk about the benefits to our environment and our own quality of life by reducing the country's population.

Let's talk about our future and where this ridiculous system of endless growth is taking us. Let's have an open debate of what kind of world we are going to leave the future generation embracing this suicidal system of endless growth.

This is going to get worse especially when the HS2 is finished for you will have businesses covering the green with more concrete then you'll have more green covered in tarmac for the car parks, then more green covering in concrete for the new housing estates.

There is no future in this, when is the human race going to wake up to this truth, or is that impossible for it to do because it is solely consumed by greed to such an extent it will happily destroy its own environment the very thing it relies on for its existence as long as individuals can have a luxury lifestyle in their lifetime., while the rest either scrape a living or wallow in poverty, because that's the system you all embrace. A system that created a segregated society, you have the few at the top rolling in absolute luxury, then you have the millions at the bottom on benefits,tax credit, unemployed living in poverty which breeds over 90% of your crime. then you have the poor sods in the middle wwho have to pay for the nose for everything feeding both ends. and these are the ones who have to live amongst the benefit culture the rich at the top don't. That is describing your system of economic growth.

Every house you build that is land that cannot breathe, that is land that cannot absorb water, that is the land where nothing can grow, that is land that is permanently dead.

There is no future in a policy that will end up covering the land in concrete and tarmac.
In 2014 I heard David Cameron say that our buildings only take up 9% of the country's landmass, then recently on a BBC programme I heard someone say we only take up 5%, and then the recent programme UK wild, one of the presenters said we only take up 3%. It's time to stop lying and start facing the truth, how can we claim to be an intelligent species when we are not capable of facing the truth.

The island we live on is not endless so why do we think we can have endless growth on it?.


My question to the people out there, is are we an intelligent species or a virus just pretending to be intelligent?


Because nothing intelligent would behave in such a way that its action would bring harm, in danger or destroy its own environment. the only lifeform I know that will destroy its own environment is a virus.

snippet.textDisplay: Weird they think that's a lot of rain there. Here in Texas we sometimes get that much in an hour (the 150mm amount they got in 2 days!). In 1993 we had a storm with 200mm in 1 hour. Our "drainage design storm of record" in the county I live in (central Texas) was from 100 yrs ago when we got 950mm (near 1 metre!) in 1 day! Imagine what that would do to Wales & England! They should tear down all homes in the floodplain and move those people to higher ground. I do love Britain though. We have our share of people living in floodplains here too.
